+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| India Hopes to Make $10 Laptops a Reality                          |
|   from the but-how-much-in-rupees dept.                            |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Friday May 04, @02:55 (Portables)        |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/04/048259      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

sas-dot writes "We all know Nicholas Negroponte's $100 [0] OLPC. India,
which was a potential market, [1]rejected it. India's Human Resources
Development ministry's [2]idea to make laptops at $10 is firmly taking
shape with two designs already in and public sector undertaking
Semiconductor Complex evincing interest to be a part of the project. So
far, the cost of one laptop, after factoring in labor charges, is coming
to $47 but the ministry feels the price will come down dramatically
considering the fact that the demand would be for one million laptops."

Discuss this story at:
    http://hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/04/048259

Links:
