| AACS Vows to Fight Bloggers                                        |
|   from the guerilla-bloggers dept.                                 |
|   posted by ScuttleMonkey on Friday May 04, @11:09 (Software)      |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/04/1330248          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Jonas Wisser writes "The BBC is carrying the story that AACS has
[1]promised to take action against those who have posted the AACS crack
online. Michael Ayers, chairperson of AACS, noted that the cracked key
has now been revoked, and went on to say, 'Some people clearly think it's
a First Amendment issue. There is no intent from us to interfere with
people's right to discuss copy protection. We respect free speech.' The
[2]AACS website tells consumers how they can 'continue to enjoy content
protected by AACS' by 'refreshing the encryption keys associated with
their HD DVD and Blu-ray software players.'"

