+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Cooler Silicon Lasers Via Energy Harvesting                        |
|   from the more-power-to-ya dept.                                  |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Friday May 04, @14:08 (Power)            |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/04/1717211     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Light Licker writes "UCLA researchers have developed [0]a way to cut
power use and heat output from a silicon laser used for optoelectronics.
Both have been problems because silicon absorbs too much light —
producing high-energy free electrons that make heat. One of Intel's best
silicon lasers produced 125 times more heat than usable light. The UCLA
team added a diode to their laser which can harvest free electrons and
use them to help power the circuit — simultaneously cutting heat output
and power use."

Discuss this story at:
    http://hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/04/1717211

Links:
    0. http://www.newscientisttech.com/article/dn11784-energy-harvesting-can-boost-optoelectronic-efficiency.html


